          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the chocolate sauce",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk the cornflour and cocoa into 100 ml of the cold milk until smooth. Bring the remaining milk, sugar, and a pinch of salt to a simmer in a saucepan. Whisk in the cornflour mixture and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add the chopped chocolate. Stir until smooth and glossy. Keep warm over very low heat.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the churro dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the flour and salt in a heatproof bowl. Add the boiling water and oil and beat vigorously with a wooden spoon until a cohesive, smooth dough forms, this takes about 2 minutes. The dough will be stiff. Immediately transfer to a piping bag fitted with a large star nozzle. Work quickly; the dough must be piped while hot.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oil in a large saucepan to 180°C. Pipe churros directly into the oil in 12 to 15 cm lengths, snipping each off with scissors. Fry 4 to 5 at a time for 2 to 3 minutes, turning halfway, until deep amber and the ridges are crisp. Drain briefly on the rack, then roll immediately in the cinnamon sugar mixture. Serve with the warm chocolate sauce for dipping.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
